text: Co-Co may refer to: * Co-Co locomotives, a code for a locomotive wheel arrangement with two six-wheeled bogies with all axles powered, with a separate motor per axle * Co-Co (band), a British pop group *"Co-Co" (Sweet song), 1971 * Co-co! Magazine, a Hong Kong magazine * Abbreviation for Contingent convertible bond ==See also== * Coco (disambiguation) * Cocoa (disambiguation) * Koko (disambiguation) * Coca (disambiguation)
title: Co-Co
